How many different values are represented by the following quantities? $$3^{-2}, 9^{-2}, 27^{-\frac{2}{3}}, 9\cdot81^{-1}, 243^{-\frac{4}{5}}$$

$$3^{-2} = \frac{1}{3^2} = \frac{1}{9}$$
$$9^{-2} = \left(3^2\right)^{-2} = 3^{-4} = \frac{1}{3^4} = \frac{1}{81}$$
$$27^{-\frac{2}{3}} = \left(3^3\right)^{-\frac{2}{3}} = 3^{-2} = \frac{1}{3^2} = \frac{1}{9}$$
$$9\cdot81^{-1} = 9\cdot\frac{1}{81} = 9\cdot\frac{1}{9^2} = 9\cdot\frac{1}{81} = \frac{9}{81} = \frac{1}{9}$$
$$243^{-\frac{4}{5}} = \left(3^5\right)^{-\frac{4}{5}} = 3^{-4} = \frac{1}{3^4} = \frac{1}{81}$$
The different values are $\frac{1}{9}$ and $\frac{1}{81}$.
There are 2 different values.
Final Answer: $\boxed{2}$
